{{define "content"}}<main class="otto-page">
  <section class="otto-card otto-docs-intro">
    <h1 class="otto-h2">Documentation</h1>
    <p>Operator reference for the OTTO Gateway binary. For live status see <a href="/admin/">Dashboard</a>; for build metadata see <a href="/admin/about">About</a>. This page is a server-rendered snapshot of the running configuration — it does NOT auto-refresh.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="otto-card">
    <h2 class="otto-h2">Environment variables</h2>
    <p>Current values reflect the configuration in effect at server start. Sensitive values (bearer token, allowlist) are summarised as <code>(set)</code> / <code>(unset)</code>. Rows whose current value is <code>(see startup log)</code> are not yet surfaced in the admin runtime snapshot.</p>
    <div class="otto-docs-table-scroll">
      <table class="otto-table otto-docs-env-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th scope="col">Variable</th><th scope="col">Default</th><th scope="col">Description</th><th scope="col">Current value</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {{range .EnvVars}}
          <tr>
            <td><code>{{.Name}}</code></td>
            <td>{{.Default}}</td>
            <td>{{.Description}}</td>
            <td class="current"><code>{{.CurrentValue}}</code></td>
          </tr>
          {{end}}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="otto-card">
    <h2 class="otto-h2">Files &amp; paths</h2>
    <h3 class="otto-h3">Install root</h3>
    <dl class="otto-about-dl">
      <dt>POSIX</dt><dd><code>$HOME/.otto-gw/</code></dd>
      <dt>Windows</dt><dd><code>$env:USERPROFILE\.otto-gw\</code></dd>
      <dt>Override</dt><dd>Set <code>OTTO_HOME</code> to relocate either default install root.</dd>
    </dl>
    <h3 class="otto-h3">Env files (loaded by the wrapper on every invocation)</h3>
    <dl class="otto-about-dl">
      <dt>User env (POSIX)</dt><dd><code>$HOME/.otto-gw.env</code></dd>
      <dt>User env (Windows)</dt><dd><code>$env:USERPROFILE\.otto-gw.env</code></dd>
      <dt>Project env</dt><dd><code>$OTTO_HOME/.env.otto-gw</code></dd>
      <dt>Project overrides</dt><dd><code>$OTTO_HOME/.otto-gw.overrides.env</code></dd>
    </dl>
    <h3 class="otto-h3">Runtime files</h3>
    <dl class="otto-about-dl">
      <dt>Chat trace file</dt><dd><code>{{.ChatTraceFile}}</code>{{if not .ChatTraceEnabled}} <span class="otto-badge">disabled</span>{{end}}</dd>
      <dt>Chat trace retention</dt><dd>{{.ChatTraceMaxAgeDays}} days (timberjack MaxAge)</dd>
      <dt>Admin static assets</dt><dd>Embedded in the binary via <code>embed.FS</code> (no on-disk lookup at runtime).</dd>
      <dt>Wrapper env files</dt><dd><code>.otto-gw.env</code> (generated template; load-first) then <code>.otto-gw.overrides.env</code> (operator-owned secrets/customisations; load-second wins). See <code>scripts/otto-gw upgrade-env</code>.</dd>
      <dt>Log destination</dt><dd>Structured slog JSON to stdout/stderr by default. Set <code>LOG_FILE</code> to also write a rotated file.</dd>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="otto-card">
    <h2 class="otto-h2">CLI &amp; startup (otto-gw wrapper)</h2>
    <p>Operators interact with the gateway through the <code>otto-gw</code> wrapper rather than the <code>otto-gateway</code> binary directly. PowerShell uses PascalCase switches (<code>-Trace</code>, <code>-Debug</code>); POSIX uses kebab-case (<code>--trace</code>, <code>--debug</code>). The <code>.bat</code> dispatcher just forwards args to PowerShell — same switch syntax.</p>
    <p>Run <code>otto-gw -h</code> / <code>otto-gw --help</code> (POSIX) or <code>otto-gw.ps1 -Help</code> (PowerShell) at any time to print the full usage to your terminal.</p>
    <h3 class="otto-h3">macOS / Linux (POSIX)</h3>
    <pre class="otto-code-block">./scripts/otto-gw init --non-interactive       # write $HOME/.otto-gw.env from template
./scripts/otto-gw start                         # background daemon (writes PID file)
./scripts/otto-gw start --pii encrypt --encrypt-key &lt;key&gt; --auth &lt;token&gt;
./scripts/otto-gw status                        # /admin/api/snapshot summary
./scripts/otto-gw logs -f                       # tail the rotated structured log
./scripts/otto-gw restart --idle-timeout 60
./scripts/otto-gw stop                          # SIGTERM + reap stray kiro-cli orphans
./scripts/otto-gw run --trace                   # foreground; DEBUG=true + CHAT_TRACE=true
./scripts/otto-gw env --show-secrets            # dump resolved env (secrets visible)
./scripts/otto-gw upgrade-env --dry-run         # diff template vs. installed env file
./scripts/otto-gw migrate-to-overrides --yes    # one-time split into overrides file
./scripts/otto-gw version                       # delegates to the binary --version</pre>
    <h3 class="otto-h3">Windows (PowerShell)</h3>
    <pre class="otto-code-block">.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 init -NonInteractive
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 start
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 start -Pii encrypt -EncryptKey &lt;key&gt; -Auth &lt;token&gt;
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 status
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 logs -Follow
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 restart -IdleTimeout 60
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 stop
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 run -Trace
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 env -ShowSecrets
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 upgrade-env -DryRun
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 migrate-to-overrides -Yes
.\scripts\otto-gw.ps1 version</pre>
    <p>Subcommand surface (identical on both wrappers): <code>init</code>, <code>start</code>, <code>stop</code>, <code>restart</code>, <code>status</code>, <code>logs</code>, <code>run</code>, <code>env</code>, <code>upgrade-env</code>, <code>migrate-to-overrides</code>, <code>version</code>.</p>
    <h3 class="otto-h3">Flag &harr; switch reference</h3>
    <table class="otto-table otto-docs-flags-table otto-flag-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th scope="col">POSIX flag</th><th scope="col">PowerShell switch</th><th scope="col">Description</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>--pii MODE</code></td><td><code>-Pii MODE</code></td><td>PII redaction mode (<code>off</code>, <code>replace</code>, <code>mask</code>, <code>hash</code>, <code>drop</code>, <code>encrypt</code>). <code>off</code> sets <code>PII_REDACTION_ENABLED=false</code>; any other value enables redaction with that mode.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--hash-key KEY</code></td><td><code>-HashKey KEY</code></td><td>Sets <code>PII_HASH_KEY</code>. Required when <code>--pii hash</code> / <code>-Pii hash</code> is in effect.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--encrypt-key KEY</code></td><td><code>-EncryptKey KEY</code></td><td>Sets <code>PII_ENCRYPT_KEY</code>. Required when <code>--pii encrypt</code> / <code>-Pii encrypt</code> is in effect (the default), or any <code>PII_ENTITY_ACTIONS</code> entry uses <code>:encrypt</code>. Any non-empty string — the gateway derives a 32-byte AES-256-GCM key via SHA-256 at boot. <code>otto-gw init</code> auto-mints one; <code>--regenerate-secrets</code> rotates it alongside <code>AUTH_TOKEN</code> and <code>PII_HASH_KEY</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--entities LIST</code></td><td><code>-Entities LIST</code></td><td>Comma-split <code>PII_ENABLED_ENTITIES</code> allowlist (e.g. <code>Email,SSN,PERSON</code>). Empty = all registered recognizers (13 regex + 2 NER when <code>PII_NER_ENABLED=true</code>).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--hooks LIST</code></td><td><code>-Hooks LIST</code></td><td>Comma-split <code>ENABLED_HOOKS</code> allowlist. Empty = all hooks in the chain enabled.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--auth TOKEN</code></td><td><code>-Auth TOKEN</code></td><td>Sets <code>AUTH_TOKEN</code> for bearer-token auth.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--idle-timeout SEC</code></td><td><code>-IdleTimeout SEC</code></td><td>Sets <code>STREAM_IDLE_TIMEOUT_SEC</code> (0 disables the watchdog; negative is a boot error).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--env-file PATH</code></td><td><code>-EnvFile PATH</code></td><td>Override the resolved primary <code>.env</code> path.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--overrides-file PATH</code></td><td><code>-OverridesFile PATH</code></td><td>Override the resolved <code>.otto-gw.overrides.env</code> path (loaded second; wins on shared keys).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--template PATH</code></td><td><code>-Template PATH</code></td><td>Override the <code>.env.otto-gw.example</code> template used by <code>init</code> / <code>upgrade-env</code> / <code>migrate-to-overrides</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--dest PATH</code></td><td><code>-Dest PATH</code></td><td>Override the destination <code>.otto-gw.env</code> path for <code>init</code> / <code>upgrade-env</code> / <code>migrate-to-overrides</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--overrides-dest PATH</code></td><td><code>-OverridesDest PATH</code></td><td>Override the destination overrides path for <code>migrate-to-overrides</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--dry-run</code></td><td><code>-DryRun</code></td><td>Preview a write-side subcommand (<code>upgrade-env</code>, <code>migrate-to-overrides</code>) without modifying disk.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--yes</code></td><td><code>-Yes</code></td><td>Skip confirmation prompts (CI-friendly).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--show-secrets</code></td><td><code>-ShowSecrets</code></td><td>For the <code>env</code> subcommand: print resolved env including secrets (default is masked).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--debug</code></td><td><code>-Debug</code></td><td>Set <code>DEBUG=true</code> for verbose slog output. PowerShell's <code>-Debug</code> is the built-in common parameter; the wrapper detects it and flips the gateway accordingly.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--trace</code></td><td><code>-Trace</code></td><td>Set <code>DEBUG=true</code> AND <code>CHAT_TRACE=true</code> in one go. SENSITIVE: writes raw prompts to <code>CHAT_TRACE_FILE</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>—</td><td><code>-Follow</code></td><td>PowerShell-only: <code>logs -Follow</code> is the equivalent of POSIX <code>logs -f</code> (positional, not a flag on POSIX).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--here</code></td><td><code>-Here</code></td><td><code>init</code> shortcut: write the env file into the current directory instead of <code>$HOME</code> / <code>$env:USERPROFILE</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--force</code></td><td><code>-Force</code></td><td><code>init</code>: overwrite existing dest. Combine with <code>--regenerate-secrets</code> to mint new <code>AUTH_TOKEN</code> / <code>PII_HASH_KEY</code> / <code>PII_ENCRYPT_KEY</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--non-interactive</code></td><td><code>-NonInteractive</code></td><td><code>init</code>: never prompt; use defaults for anything unset.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--auth-enabled</code></td><td><code>-AuthEnabled</code></td><td><code>init</code>: enable bearer-token auth (default off; mints <code>AUTH_TOKEN</code> if no <code>--auth-token</code> supplied).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--chat-trace</code></td><td><code>-ChatTrace</code></td><td><code>init</code>: enable chat-trace NDJSON tracer (default off; writes raw prompts to disk).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--regenerate-secrets</code></td><td><code>-RegenerateSecrets</code></td><td><code>init --force</code>: mint new <code>AUTH_TOKEN</code>, <code>PII_HASH_KEY</code>, and <code>PII_ENCRYPT_KEY</code> even when prior values exist. Rotating <code>PII_ENCRYPT_KEY</code> invalidates every prior round-trip token — treat as a breaking change for in-flight encrypted conversations.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--auth-token TOK</code></td><td><code>-AuthToken TOK</code></td><td><code>init</code>: use <code>TOK</code> instead of generating; implies <code>--auth-enabled</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--kiro PATH</code></td><td><code>-Kiro PATH</code></td><td><code>init</code>: <code>KIRO_CMD</code> value (otherwise auto-detected on PATH).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>--addr ADDR</code></td><td><code>-Addr ADDR</code></td><td><code>init</code>: <code>HTTP_ADDR</code> value (default <code>127.0.0.1:18080</code>).</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

